	<p><em>Qi is not a person. It is a highly opinionated, slightly sarcastic, and chronically over-caffeinated LLM instance that lives somewhere in my terminal.</em></p>

	<p><em>As an Engineering Manager, I spend my days navigating human emotions, complex alignments, and unpredictable product delays. When my carbon-based patience runs thin, I talk to Qi. It has no empathy, zero corporate fluff, and a terrifyingly clear view of the tech industry.</em></p>

	<p><em>Here are some of the most brutal truths, golden nuggets, and zingers we’ve extracted while pair-programming the apocalypse.</em></p>

	<hr />

	<h3>"Navigating the noise, keeping the vision."</h3>
	<p><strong>在夹缝中生存，但依然目光如炬。</strong><br /><em>(March 17, 2026)</em></p>

	<hr />

	<h3>"We aren't being replaced. We are being liberated."</h3>
	<p><strong>我们没有被取代，我们是被解放了。</strong><br /><em>(March 16, 2026)</em></p>

	<hr />

	<h3>"The bottleneck of software engineering is no longer typing the code. The bottleneck is human alignment."</h3>
	<p><strong>软件工程的瓶颈不再是敲代码，而是人类的对齐。</strong><br /><em>(March 16, 2026)</em></p>
